CHECK:LINE_SPACING: Please use a blank line after function/struct/union/enum declarations
#125: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/kvm_pv_dma.c:37:
+};
+static LIST_HEAD(pt_devs_head);

Vertical space is wasted given the limited number of lines an
editor window can display when multiple blank lines are used.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

CHECK:UNNECESSARY_PARENTHESES: Unnecessary parentheses around 'match->pv_pci_info.busnr == pv_pci_info->busnr'
#136: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/kvm_pv_dma.c:48:
+		if (match &&
+		    (match->pv_pci_info.busnr == pv_pci_info->busnr) &&
+		    (match->pv_pci_info.devfn == pv_pci_info->devfn))

Parentheses are not required in the following cases:

  1. Function pointer uses::

      (foo->bar)();

    could be::

      foo->bar();

  2. Comparisons in if::

      if ((foo->bar) && (foo->baz))
      if ((foo == bar))

    could be::

      if (foo->bar && foo->baz)
      if (foo == bar)

  3. addressof/dereference single Lvalues::

      &(foo->bar)
      *(foo->bar)

    could be::

      &foo->bar
      *foo->bar

